import React,{ Fragment }  from 'react';

    List,
    SimpleForm,
    TextField,
    TextInput,

require('react-dom');
window.React2 = require('react');
console.log("-----compare------")
console.log(window.React1 === window.React2);



/**
 *
 * editing specified user.
 *
 * @param props

 */

    <Edit  {...props}>
        <SimpleForm >
                        <TextInput disabled source="addressid"/>

                        <TextField disabled source="immatdate"  />
                        <TextField disabled source="examatdate"/>
                        <TextField disabled source="exmatreason"/>
                        <TextField disabled source="degreecode"/>
                        <TextField disabled source="degree"/>
                        <TextField disabled source="university"/>
                        <TextField disabled source="capr_nameeng"/>
                        <TextField disabled source="capr_degreeshort"/>
                        <TextField disabled source="isnotifiale"/>
        </SimpleForm>
    </Edit>
);


/**
 *
 * @param props
 * @returns {*}
 * @constructor
 */
export const StudiumList = (props) => (

    <Fragment>
        <List {...props} >
          <Datagrid >
              <TextField source="addressid"/>

              <TextField disabled source="immatdate"  />
              <TextField disabled source="examatdate"/>
              <TextField disabled source="exmatreason"/>
              <TextField disabled source="degreecode"/>
              <TextField disabled source="degree"/>
              <TextField disabled source="university"/>
              <TextField disabled source="capr_nameeng"/>
              <TextField disabled source="capr_degreeshort"/>
              <TextField disabled source="isnotifiale"/>

              </Datagrid>
        </List>
    </Fragment>

);
